# 1Ô∏è. TAR - Archive Utility

## Important Options

| Option | Meaning |
|--------|----------|
| -c | Create archive |
| -x | Extract archive |
| -v | Verbose |
| -f | File name |
| -t | List contents |
| -z | Gzip compression |
| -j | Bzip2 compression |

---

## Practical 1: Create and Extract TAR File

### Create Test Directory

```bash
mkdir /test1
touch /test1/sample{1..10}.java
ls /test1
```

### Create TAR Archive

```bash
tar -cvf backup1.tar /test1
ls -l
```

### List TAR Contents

```bash
tar -tvf backup1.tar
```

### Extract TAR File

```bash
cp backup1.tar /usr/
cd /usr
tar -xvf backup1.tar
ls -l
```

---

# 2Ô∏è. Compression with GZIP & BZIP2

## Create GZIP Archive

```bash
tar -zcvf backup1.tar.gz /test1
ls -lah
```

## View GZIP Archive Contents

```bash
tar -tvf backup1.tar.gz
```

---

## Create BZIP2 Archive

```bash
tar -jcvf backup1.tar.bz2 /test1
ls -lah
```

## View BZIP2 Archive

```bash
tar -tvf backup1.tar.bz2
```

---

# 3Ô∏è. ZIP and UNZIP

## Install ZIP (if not installed)

```bash
dnf install zip unzip -y
```

---

## Create ZIP Archive

```bash
mkdir /test2
touch /test2/sample{1..10}.java

zip test2.zip /test2/*
ls -l
```

---

## Extract ZIP File

```bash
unzip test2.zip
ls -l
```

---

# 4Ô∏è. Cron Task: Backup /etc/passwd Daily at 5 PM

## Manual Backup with Timestamp

```bash
tar -zcvf /tmp/backup_passwd_$(date +%d_%b_%Y).tar.gz /etc/passwd
```

Example:

```
backup_passwd_22_Feb_2026.tar.gz
```

---

## Automate Using Cron

Edit crontab:

```bash
crontab -e
```

Add this line:
```bash
0 17 * * * /usr/bin/tar -zcvf /tmp/backup_passwd_$(/usr/bin/date +\%d_\%b_\%Y).tar.gz /etc/passwd
```

---

# üìå Summary

In this practical, we:

- Created TAR archives
- Applied GZIP and BZIP2 compression
- Created and extracted ZIP files
- Automated backup using Cron
- Used timestamp-based naming for dynamic backups

